# Deployment Architecture

Two-region setup: **Railway** (primary, full AI processing) + **RU edge** (ru.ailookstudio.ru, proxies AI to primary).

## Key invariants

- `deploy/ru/update.sh` is the **single source of truth** for RU deploys. CI calls it via SSH; never duplicate its logic inline.
- Alembic migrations run on **both** primary and edge at startup (`src/main.py` lifespan). Never use `create_all` in production.
- `DEPLOY_GIT_SHA` must be passed to both backend (`environment:` in docker-compose) and frontend (`ARG` in web/Dockerfile). Verify via `/health` (backend) and `/version.json` (frontend).
- Frontend is built inside Docker (`web/Dockerfile`), extracted to a named volume (`ratemeai_web_dist`), and served by nginx. Use `--no-cache` for web builds to avoid stale layers.

## Deployment flow

```
git push main
  -> CI: test -> deploy-backend (Railway) -> deploy-ru (SSH -> update.sh)
  -> update.sh: git pull -> build web --no-cache -> extract to volume -> build+restart app -> restart nginx -> health check
  -> CI: smoke tests (health SHA, version.json, catalog API, auth + tasks endpoint)
```

## Verifying a deploy

```bash
# Backend version and git SHA
curl https://ru.ailookstudio.ru/health
# Frontend build SHA and timestamp
curl https://ru.ailookstudio.ru/version.json
# DB-dependent endpoint (proves migrations ran)
curl https://ru.ailookstudio.ru/api/v1/catalog/styles?mode=dating
```

## Adding a migration

1. Create migration: `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"`
2. Review in `alembic/versions/`
3. Push to main -- both Railway and RU edge apply it on next startup

## Manual RU deploy

```bash
ssh user@ru-server
cd /opt/ratemeai
sudo DEPLOY_GIT_SHA=$(git rev-parse --short=12 HEAD) ./deploy/ru/update.sh
```
